Actually this problem happened when I tried to set a (valid) cursor to the SimpleCursorAdapter linked to my spinner. I'll try to reproduce it later on the code of Bug #458. And, as I said, the spinner was in the ActionBar, implemented as an ActionProvider.
I fixed it through a workaround implementing the newDropDownView function on my SimpleCursorAdapter, as follows:
java
@Override
public View newDropDownView(Context context, Cursor cursor, ViewGroup parent) {
    View ret = super.newDropDownView(context, cursor, parent);
    ret.setLayoutParams(new ListView.LayoutParams(screenWidth, LayoutParams.WRAP_CONTENT));
    return ret;
}
