eduardb:
It seems that calling super.setChecked(checked); last in Switch.setChecked(boolean) resolves the problem. Works both on Android 2.1 and 4.2.2, and hopefully doesn't have any negative effects. This issue is present in Android source code too.
Should I make a pull request, or you will make the fix yourself? This is how the function should look:
android
@Override
    public void setChecked(boolean checked) {        
        mThumbPosition = checked ? getThumbScrollRange() : 0;
        invalidate(); 
        super.setChecked(checked);
    }
PS: Thanks for this awesome library :)
